headline: Merck: FDA grants Breakthrough Therapy designation to sacituzumab tirumotecan
summary: Merck (MRK) announced that the U.S. FDA has granted Breakthrough Therapy designation to sacituzumab tirumotecan for the treatment of patients with advanced or metastatic nonsquamous non-small cell lung cancer with epidermal growth factor receptor mutations whose disease progressed on or after tyrosine kinase inhibitor and platinum-based chemotherapy. Sac-TMT is an investigational trophoblast cell-surface antigen 2-directed antibody drug conjugate being developed in collaboration with Kelun-Biote
